SUMMARY:945 after Butter n Eggs Parade
DESCRIPTION:Meet 945—a band with alt-rock roots\, bold emotional voice\, and a live show that hits both heart and floor. Emerging from Sonoma County’s rock scene\, they merge the raw energy of 1990s/2000s alt rock with modern ideas and a hauntingly strong female lead vocal. \nLead singer (raised in Petaluma)\, Sophia’s voice is one of the band’s core charms—dynamic\, raw\, honest\, capable of whisper-quiet emotion and full-tilt rocker power. Backed by stellar instrumentation and songwriting that deals in real life\, 945 delivers originals and reinterpretations that stay with you. \nToday’s show will feel like you’re front-row for a band on the brink; fun\, powerful\, and unafraid to hold you. Rock favorites\, fresh originals\, and that kind of performance that echoes well past the set-end. \nWhy You’ve Gotta Be Here after the parade: \nAlt rock with soul—fierce\, real\, and moving \nA band already earning accolades (Best Rock Band for 2 years in a row and best lead vocals for 3 years in a row through Bohemian Magazine)
URL:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/945-after-butter-n-eggs-parade/
LOCATION:The Big Easy\, 128 American Alley\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
CATEGORIES:Alternative Rock
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_9743.jpeg
END:VEVENT
